The paper deals with the problem of approximate string matching allowing for unbalanced translocations of adjacent factors. This problem involves the manipulation of strings and their subsequences, which is a typical topic in computer science. The use of dynamic programming and directed acyclic word graphs suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and graph theory (cs.GT).
